      "text": [
        " سَلَمٍ إِذَا أَسْلَمَ فِي طَعَامٍ أَوْ مَتَاعٍ أَوْ حَيَوَانٍ فَقَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَنْ تَسْتَوْثِقَ مِنْ مَالِكَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3942 - Sama'ah asked him about a pledge (rahn) that a man gives as security in a salam transaction when he advances payment for food, goods, or animals.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in securing your wealth.\""
        ]
      }
